org.archive.wayback.accesscontrol

Interface ContextExclusionFilterFactory

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ExclusionFilterFactory
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CompositeExclusionFilterFactory, OraclePolicyService

    public interface ContextExclusionFilterFactory
extends ExclusionFilterFactory
    Extended ExclusionFilterFactory interface for configuring ExclusionFilter instance depending on context information.

    If an ExclusionFilterFactory instance also implements this interface, and if appropriate ExclusionContext is available, caller shall getExclusionFilter(CollectionContext) method instead of ExclusionFilterFactory.get(). This is for migrating to new interface maintaining compatibility with existing code. Eventually all ExclusionFilterFactory implementation should migrate to this interface.

    Typically context corresponds to one of web archive collection hosted by the same Wayback instance.
